@ontology-search/scenario-viewer-wasm
======================================

This package vendors, builds and wraps a WebAssembly build of the **esmini**
OpenSCENARIO player so an authored `.xosc` can be previewed in the browser.

Third-party component
---------------------

  Component : esmini (EnvironmentSimulator) — the esminiJS Emscripten target
  Upstream  : https://github.com/esmini/esmini
  Pin       : commit 77028d83e6d402de52f7187e5384d1b1c02b7d1f (branch master)
  Path      : EnvironmentSimulator/Libraries/esminiJS
  License   : Mozilla Public License, Version 2.0 (MPL-2.0)

esmini is licensed under the Mozilla Public License, Version 2.0. A copy of the
license is distributed with the upstream source (LICENSE file at the repository
root) and is also available at https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/MPL/2.0/.

The prebuilt artifact `wasm/esmini.js` is the unmodified Emscripten output of
compiling the esmini source at the pinned commit (see `native/BUILD.md` for the
exact, reproducible recipe). It is committed here — like the Oxigraph WASM in
`packages/sparql` and the OpenSCENARIO engine WASM in `packages/authoring-wasm`
— so that CI never needs the C++ toolchain.

MPL-2.0 is a file-level (weak) copyleft. The esmini source files remain under
MPL-2.0; the build applies one small, documented portability patch to esmini's
own `esminiJS/CMakeLists.txt` (`native/patches/0001-esminijs-version-cmake.patch`)
which is offered upstream (see `native/BUILD.md`). The TypeScript facade under
`src/` is an independent work that merely *uses* the compiled module across the
JS/WASM boundary and is licensed under this repository's license.

Build reproducibility
---------------------

The pin (`versions.json`) plus `native/BUILD.md` + `native/build.mjs` reproduce
`wasm/esmini.js` from the pinned submodule. `wasm/esmini.js.sha256` is the
integrity manifest checked by `native/verify-checksum.mjs` (run in CI on every
PR — the one file here a reviewer cannot read in a diff).
